Reliance Capital May Consider Selling a 26% Stake in Funds Unit

-- B y   S h i k h a r   B a l w a n i
-- 
2011-09-28T04:28:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/reliance-capital-may-consider-selling-a-26-stake-in-funds-unit.html
Reliance Capital Ltd. (RCAPT)  will look to
sell a 26 percent stake in its asset management unit “at some
point in time,” Chief Executive Officer Sam Ghosh said.  The company is in discussions with Japan’s Nippon Life
Insurance Co. for working in three areas, Ghosh said in an
interview broadcast on Bloomberg UTV today.  Reliance Capital is in talks to sell a stake in Reliance
Capital Asset Management Ltd. to Nippon, Chairman  Anil Ambani 
told shareholders at the company’s annual general meeting
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shikhar Balwani in Mumbai at 
 sbalwani@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
